values:
I survived the zombie apocalypse!

Hopefully I'll survive the next one later this quarter.

"Banjo Kazooie: Nuts & Bolts was Rare's third idea in their plans to create a sequel to Banjo-Tooie. In an interview with Gregg Mayles, he said that the first idea was to create a remake of Banjo-Kazooie that would purport to be a direct port, but would feature extreme changes unexpectedly. For example, a massive queen termite would emerge from the termite hill in Mumbo's Mountain, causing Banjo to have to get oranges for Conga to throw at it. The second concept involved more traditional platforming, but with Gruntilda trying to follow Banjo and Kazooie around every world and replicating their moves in an effort to better them."


WHO thought that a racing game would be better than those first two ideas and why did anybody listen to him?
YOU PUT THE LIME IN THE COCONUT AND DRINK THEM BOTH UP/YOU PUT THE LIME IN THE COCONUT AND DRINK THEM BOTH UP

Sonic, he can really move

Sonic, he's got an attitude

Sonic, he's the fastest thing ali-i-ive

I had a nightmare where my desktop was covered with icons that completely filled the screen, and I wanted to clean them up, but I used them all to often to delete them, and there was nowhere else that I could move them to. It was horrible.
I'm watching National Treasure 2 on my DS. This rules.
Circus Contraption was brilliant. I highly recommend it to everyone.

So, turns out Mass Effect is just as awesome as everyone says it is. 

That is all.

I hear latte orders as I fall asleep. I dream that I am at the register and people are telling me what they want. Even when I realize that it's a dream and try to get away they still bitch at me that they haven't gotten their coffee yet. My feet hurt all the time. I can't get the smell of coffee grounds out of my clothes. I have nothing interesting to talk about because the job never changes and it's all I do.

I can't WAIT to get back to school.

On the bright side, DOLLA DOLLA BILLS Y'ALL!
OOOOOOOMG THEY PUT MUSE IN ROCK BAND
I will likely be going to Olympia on the 30th for Neal's party. Anyone who wants to come with should talk to me.
I love the Comcast pun commercials. They are brilliant.
There was a chick who worked on her laptop in Tully's today for about 7 hours who looked JUST like Boomer. Any time I got bored I would look at her and get a kick out of this fact.

Of significantly less importance, but a similar level of awesomeness to my last entry, is there anyone who knows enough about photoshop or anything like that to help me with this image?

It was an entry in a contest on shirt.woot.com that never got made into a shirt, but I really want it. I want to take it to one of those places like printfection where they put your image on a t-shirt, but the image is low rez and partially obscured by the little preview image, which in turn has an even lower-rez version of the image including the obscured part. 

I know there's some way to use image-voodoo on this to fix it, but I have no idea how.
July 10th. Boston, and to a lesser degree of excitement, Styx. $62. TOTALLY worth it.

Bear Grylls should be president. He could win wars single-handedly.

EDIT: Excuse me, Lieutenant Commander Bear Grylls.
The White Stripes had better not actually be broken up or I'm gonna have to bust some skulls.
I god an interview tomorrow, and it's not to see if I'm good enough to hire, it's to see if there's any reason not to hire me!
Today's lesson learned: death metal bands should not cover classic rock albums.

While sitting at our computers playing N:

Oisin: I CAN"T TAKE 3 AT ONCE!

me: ...

*laughter*
Does  anyone know where I could get a bright crimson Cougars hoodie without actually going to WSU?

Best  Buy is a really terrible name.

Also, I love Styx.
I get to spend Christmas Eve at Disneyland!
'EY! DID THAT LAD JUST SAY RINGS ARE COOL?!
The atomic bomb was developed in less than the amount of time that Duke Nukem forever has been in developement.
This just in: turns out Chaos are actually awesome.
I can't tell if Hayseed Dixie are geniuses or a HORRIBLE ABOMINATION of music.
NOBODY BETTER GO SEE NATURAL TREASURE 2 WITHOUT ME

SO HERE WE STAND WITH OUR BLOOD ON OUR HANDS
WE FOUGHT SO HARD NOW CAN WE UNDERSTAND
AND BREAK THE SEAL OF THIS CURSE IF I POSSIBLY CAN
FOR FREEDOM OF EVERY MAN

SO FAR AWAY WE WAIT FOR THE DAY
FOR THE LIGHTS ARE SO WASTED AND GONE
WE FEEL THE PAIN OF A LIFETIME LOST IN A THOUSAND DAYS
THROUGH THE FIRE AND THE FLAMES WE CARRY ON
So Mat and I are definitely going to The Hives. Anyone else want to go?

I don't know why I ever stopped reading Snow Crash. I haven't read a book this fast since I discovered the internet.

Also, it's good to see Alan Tudyk getting work.
